<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6174: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-12T13:00:00+08:00">April 12, 1933—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 12—12:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>321. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“April 11, 8 p.m. Army spokesman announced: <list>
                                        <label>1.</label>
                                        <item>That general attack along the Wall has been in
                                            progress since April 10th in order definitely to
                                            suppress Chinese counterattacks.</item>
                                        <label>2.</label>
                                        <item>That Lengkou was captured this morning and that
                                            Japanese are advancing toward Chienchangying.</item>
                                        <label>3.</label>
                                        <item>That aeroplanes bombarded Chinese base of operations
                                            at Dolonor.”</item>
                                    </list></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>